  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). Evidence carries one explicitly-flagged gap in model-input uncertainty bounds (wide 95% CI on blood viscosity rheological parameters), documented honestly with sensitivity analysis rationale and accepted as residual risk with full offset justification.",
